title: For Sale:  CZ SP-01 Compact
postcontent: This is a limited production pistol from CZ. My understanding is that only 500 were produced. This is similar to a CZ P-01, except that the frame is steel and it has a safety instead of a decoker, which allows for cocked-and-locked capability. I bought it for shooting in defensive pistol matches. but find the 38 ounce weight a bit too much for my shooting. The pistol has been worked over by polishing many components and adding these parts from Cajun Gun Works: comp hammer and pins, 85 trigger, floating trigger pin, light trigger spring, TS extended left side safety, and hardened firing pin retaining pin. I also have a 11.5 and 13 pound mainsprings although the stock spring is installed now. To maintain reliable ignition with the lighter springs, I think a light firing pin spring would be needed, and possible an extended firing pin. I put 100 rounds thru the pistol and found it very accurate. There are 2 14 round mags, the factory case, cleaing rods, and paperwork. I'm asking $750 with all the CGW goodies installed and will include the stock parts.
